quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  4,66,"If We had commanded them, \"Lay down your lives or leave your dwellings,\" they would have not done it, save a few of them. If they had done what they were instructed to do, it would have been better for them, as well as more strengthening [for their faith]"
  4,67,and We would have given them a great reward of Our own
  4,68,and guided them to a straight path
  4,69,"Whoever obeys God and the Messenger will be among those He has blessed: the messengers, the truthful, the witnesses, and the righteous. What excellent companions these are"
  4,70,That is God's favour. Sufficient is God's infinite knowledge
  4,71,"You who believe, take your precautions and then go forth in small groups or go forth all together"
  4,72,"Among you are some who lag behind and if you encounter a setback, they say, \"God has been gracious to me; I was not present with them"
  4,73,"But if, by God's grace, good fortune should be your lot, they will say, \"If only I had been with them I should have achieved a great success,\" as if no affection had existed between you and them"
  4,74,"Let those who would exchange the life of this world for the Hereafter, fight for the cause of God; whoever fights for the cause of God, whether he is slain or is victorious, to him We shall give a great reward"